# Content Management Guide

## Content Collections

Content is managed through Astro's content collections defined in [src/content.config.ts](mdc:src/content.config.ts).

### Blog Posts (`src/content/posts/`)
**Required frontmatter:**
```yaml
---
title: "Post Title"           # String, required
published: 2025-01-27        # Date, required (YYYY-MM-DD format)
tags: ["tag1", "tag2"]       # Array of strings, optional (defaults to [])
draft: false                 # Boolean, optional (defaults to false)
description: "Brief desc"    # String, optional (for SEO)
author: "Author Name"        # String, optional
coverImage:                  # Object, optional
  src: ./image.jpg          # Image file
  alt: "Alt text"           # String
---
```

### Work/Portfolio Items (`src/content/works/`)
**Required frontmatter:**
```yaml
---
title: "Project Title"       # String, required
type: "work"                # Enum: "work" | "oss" | "presentation" | "other"
date: 2025-01-01            # Date, required
description: "Project desc"  # String, required
link: "https://example.com"  # URL string, optional
tags: ["React", "TypeScript"] # Array of strings, optional
featured: true               # Boolean, optional (defaults to false)
coverImage:                  # Object, optional
  src: ./image.jpg          # Image file
  alt: "Alt text"           # String
---
```

### Special Content Files
- [src/content/home.md](mdc:src/content/home.md) - Homepage content with optional avatar and GitHub calendar
- [src/content/addendum.md](mdc:src/content/addendum.md) - Additional content section

